title: For Sale:  WWII Remington Rand M1911A1 w/ Original Box
postcontent:
1945 Remington Rand M1911A1 2450407 

Original and unaltered. This is the highest serial numbered Remington Rand I have ever owned. One of the few, original boxed examples from my personal collection. Parkerized 3rd style slide address Remington Rand produced in July 1945. This pistol is in excellent condition and still retains its original WWII shipping box. There were pistols sold through the D.C.M. to members of the N.R.A. in the 1960s in this serial range, that when received, were nearly new condition and included the original Remington Rand shipping boxes. This appears to be one of those pistols because of its high condition and box.

By 1945, Remington Rand was a high speed M1911A1 production line. During WWII, they produced more than 877,000 pistols between late 1942 and the end of production in 1945. This pistol has a Parkerized finish and all late war parts. The mainspring housing and slide stop are serrated. The original High Standard barrel is HS and "P" proof marked. This pistol has all original parts and perfectly matching wear patterns, some of which are simply from long tern storage in the original box.

title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson .38 hand ejector model of 1905 4th Change
postcontent:
I have a smith and wesson .38 hand ejector model of 1905, 4th change. Its obvisoulsy in used condition and is in original unrestored condition. It has all original parts and all the serial numbers match to include the original grips. This gun was produced from 1915 to 1942 and this one has a 5 inch barrel and a 6 shot. The serial numbers on this model rangwe from 241704 to 1000000, mine is 381***, putting it earlier in the production time frame, probably around early 1920's based on grips. It is a military and police gun and is in good functioning condition. This is in nickel finish.

Like I said it is obviously used but in original condition and you can see from the pictures that some of the nickel finish is wearing on the one side. "Smith and Wesson" is stamped on one side of the barrel and the other side of barrel is stamped with "38 S & W SPECIAL CTG." It has the USA patent on top of the barrel. As you can see its all complete and here with all orginal parts and unrestored. I considered this a collectable gun.

This gun is graded between fair and good condition as it still has most of the original nickel finish and still functions. This gun was probably carried by some sheriff's back in the day and no telling what this gun has seen.

Do a simple search and you will see these guns selling anywhere from 400 to 700 dollars.

I am looking for 400 dollars as this gun is a true piece of American history, send me a reply if your interested and Ill get back with you right away as my phone receives emails. 

I live around the Umatilla area of Lake County which is in central Florida.

The barrel incorporates a "birdcage" style flash suppressor/compensator with closed bottom to eliminate dust signature when firing in the prone position. The M16A2 sight system, with two flip-up apertures designed for either short range shots at moving targets or long distance accuracy, offers adjustment for windage and elevation. The elevation adjustments are graduated from 300 to 800 meters and automatically compensate for bullet drop. Forged, lightweight 7075T6 aircraft quality aluminum receivers have all M16A2 design improvements including cartridge case deflector, last round bolt hold-open and raised ridges for magazine release button protection.

The A3 Type differs in that it''s Upper Receiver is "flat-top" style with an integral Picatinny rail to offer a variety of sight, scope or night vision mounting options. A 1/2 M.o.A. rear sight is incorporated into the Removable Carrying Handle (included).

title: For Sale/Trade:  1987 Chevrolet Van, amazing condition, ATeam Style (needs Motor) read more below
postcontent:
For Sale: 1987 Chevrolet G10 van with 101,000 miles on it. The van was owned by the same person for most of its life and the second owner bought it shortly before me. I bought the van for a project as it needs a new motor and I never got around to doing anything with it. 

Recently the second owner had an issue with the engine and the mechanics shop told them it needed to be replaced. The owner decided that with their age and living on a fixed income they did not want to put any more money into the van. Within the last year they purchased a new fuel pump and had the driver's side door lock repaired. The battery in it was recycled as it was older, not holding a good charge and was likely to leak.

I was not worried about the van needing an engine as it currently has a six cylinder and I wanted to upgrade it to an eight. If you are someone that does not mind a six, the engine might need some work, and might not be shot. It is possible the shop was playing games, but I am not sure.

All of the vans fluids look clean (Transmission, coolant, power steering, etc.) Between the condition of the body and how clean the transmission fluid was I jumped on buying this van. It is really hard to find a van from this time period that is not completed rusted and rotted out. The van does not have power accessories or air conditioning like most vans from that time period. The van also has met the states stringent emissions standards as it has a current NJ Inspection Sticker on the lower driver's front windshield. The Exhaust system and underneath of the van is really in great shape.

While this van does have some rust spots on it, it is the best condition 80's van I have ever seen. The undercarriage is in great shape and the shocks are not fully rusted out like every other van I have ever seen. I really doubt the original owner drove this in the snow often. 

This van is a perfect candidate to be transformed into the A-Team van. It also has a sliding side door with a window and has the black (not stainless) trim around the back window. This vehicle qualifies for historic license plates from the State of NJ, if you decide you do not want to make it into a daily driver. For some reason I am unable to load pictures however if you are interested please let me know where you are from so I know you're not spam and I'll get pictures out to you ASAP.
